<br>
Hello guys,<br>
<br>
  I have no idea if any of these email addresses will actually get through, but lets hope one does.  Please forward to the appropriate authority if you don't handle stuff like this.<br>
<br>
  Let me try to be as brief as possible as I am sure you are rather busy folks.<br>
<br>
  I am the author of EQAnnounce, aka Glimwin Nettlefoot of the Xev server.<br>
<br>
  I am writing you this email to get an idea if a program I have written violates *in any way* the EULA.  I do not believe that it does, but I would like your assessment and feedback.  I disclose my in-game name as I would rather this all be an &quot;above-board&quot; discussion.<br>
<br>
  Let me give you a brief run-down of what it does:<br>
<br>
  1)  It is a _log.txt and notes.txt parser.<br>
  2)  It runs while the game is running watching these files.<br>
  3)  Based on configurable settings the user provides via /note commands in-game, it provides feedback via the microsoft text-to-speech engine.  Namely, creating a timer, watching for a keyword in a log file, and gathering damage stats.<br>
  4)  Users can create 'timers' which fire after a given period of time (that they provide - I've have been asked to keep a database of spawn timers which I have declined as right now it kind of forces the user to already know when a spawn/spell is about to fire - ie - requires a brain)<br>
  5)  Users can get damage feedback from the log files.  ala &quot;You did 500 points of damage at 10 points per second&quot;.<br>
<br>
  Things I would like you to assess would be:<br>
<br>
  a)  Does it violate the EULA (in my best approximation &quot;no&quot;)<br>
  b)  If so, does everything it does violate? or if some pieces can remain -- you tell me which please.<br>
<br>
  c)  If there is some violation, pity on my character, as I am writing to you in full faith of this discussion being &quot;above-board&quot; to actually get constructive feedback.  Should your findings say the whole thing violates the EULA - I will shut it down promptly.<br>
<br>
  A few key notes:<br>
<br>
  The main web-site:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqannounce.freeservers.com">eqannounce.freeservers.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
  The message boards:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub92.ezboard.com/beqannounce">pub92.ezboard.com/beqannounce</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
  Currently, in one of the forums I am trying to take a poll with those that have found it useful as to whether I should just send you the source to it.  Even that I don't have a problem with.  I just would like some of this in the client, truthfully.<br>
<br>
  I already know of GM programs that are log parsers for in-game note taking (was a guide apprentice for a while until I decided I just didn't have time to do that, play, and have a family), so am assuming this doesn't violate.<br>
<br>
  Truthfully, I am not looking for you to &quot;bless&quot; it, as I honestly could see all of the legal ramifications that could impose if you &quot;blessed&quot; it, then I (were I malicious), stuck some nasty code in there.  I would never do that, but in the essence of your protection can understand not &quot;blessing&quot; it.<br>
<br>
  All I would like to know is where it stands regarding the EULA.  I don't want to get any of the people that would like to use it banned.<br>
<br>
  I am not in a hurry for a response - please take your time and read the website, and the message boards to see what / how people would actually use it.  If there is vengeance to be had regarding it, please only take it out on me instead of the other people that have posted on the boards.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time,<br>
<br>
